Author: doteth
Content:
Hello everyone! 😀 

**Introducing the Ocean Data Bounty**
Helping data providers to package, price and market their data.

With the latest version of Ocean Protocol — OceanONDA V4 live, we are announcing a new initiative to accelerate the adoption of Ocean as the orchestration layer for Data and AI. The Ocean Data Bounty program seeks to expedite the shift into a New Data Economy by incentivising data-driven insights and the building of algorithms on datasets geared toward solving complex business challenges.

The following blog post gives an overview of:

1) Ocean’s vision driving the program
2) Ocean bounty phases
3) Expected process and benefits.

https://blog.oceanprotocol.com/introducing-the-ocean-data-bounty-7eb1e3bf3c0a

For questions, feel free to use this channel or refer to this document below 👇  https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/11FUUl3wzqtXMcaz6XUbtR8XL_03WdpWVRE0tXPKvnvY/edit#gid=1897861272

Author: bhalisa
Content:
Hey @Andrea | Ocean Protocol ,

When performing feature selection analysis, do we have to perform ALL the recommended analysis methods (graphical method (times series) & advanced methods (anova, based on correlation, etc.), or we are at liberty to choose between the two methods?

Similarly in the time series analysis, do we have to use the previous graphical methods to identify trends AND develop a model (ARIMA, Prophet, other regressors), or we can choose between the two methods?

It is stated in the description of the challenge: "You MUST AT LEAST perform the graphical methods described below in order to be considered for the competition."

Does this mean we have to do what is described under 'Graphical Method'? or it means we can choose to do that which is described as 'Potential Advanced Methods' instead?

Author: doteth
Content:
When performing feature selection analysis, do we have to perform ALL the recommended analysis methods (graphical method (times series) & advanced methods (anova, based on correlation, etc.), or we are at liberty to choose between the two methods? **@user’s discretion**

Similarly in the time series analysis, do we have to use the previous graphical methods to identify trends AND develop a model (ARIMA, Prophet, other regressors), or we can choose between the two methods? **@user’s discretion**

It is stated in the description of the challenge: “You MUST AT LEAST perform the graphical methods described below in order to be considered for the competition.” Does this mean we have to do what is described under ‘Graphical Method’? or it means we can choose to do that which is described as ‘Potential Advanced Methods’ instead? 
**Users must perform at least that. Doing more would potentially give him a higher score.**

Author: baghold
Content:
The reason you see the inner as `12345` and outer as `12345.0` is because there are missing values in the column. I assume the dataset was processed using a library such as Pandas, because `NaN` is a float and a column of integers would automatically get casted to float.

Author: 0xblockboy
Content: When looking at the marketplace how do I know if a dataset is updated daily? Because a lot of assets say they are but their metadata history at the bottom will say last updated months ago

Author: nickscavuzzo33
Content: hey @0xBlockBoy  🏴  can you link to the example you are looking at? If it is updated daily then it would show in metadata history, if not it might just be raw dat a

Author: white_rider_
Content: It's not necessarily the case. When the URL points to an endpoint that retrieves data, updates can occur even if the asset's metadata remains the same.

Author: white_rider_
Content: So for example, with a GraphQL published asset, you won't need to modify the asset's metadata to access updated data. When a query is sent to your server, the server can retrieve the most recent data based on the specific query and parameters without the need for metadata changes. This flexibility allows for efficient and dynamic data retrieval while keeping the asset's metadata unchanged.

Content:
**Quick update on the existing ‘vegetation health’ data challenge:**

We will move the Deadline 1 extra day to tomorrow night to submit your entry. This is because of a new process on delights, please pay attention to these 4 points:

1. You will need Desights Profile to submit. If you don't have one follow this tutorial to get one: https://docs.desights.ai/guides/creating-desights-profile
2. Before submitting make sure you have the valid asset URL for your submission. Here's how to do that: https://docs.desights.ai/guides/checking-if-your-asset-url-is-correct
3.If you want to get Bonus reward, Make sure to publish your asset in Ocean Market with 250 OCEAN price on Polygon network (important). And don't forget to list your bonus asset's Ocean Market url in the Submission form (very important). Here's how to publish your asset to Ocean Market for Bonus reward: https://docs.oceanprotocol.com/user-guides/publish-data-nfts
4. Make sure you submit correctly. From this challenge onwards, submission is directly via Desights Platform. Check out our guide on how to submit your solutions - https://docs.desights.ai/guides/submission-to-the-challenge 
Important -> Make sure you submit your solutions before deadline. Submission form will not be available on Desights platform once the challenge expires (its not a google form).
